
INSTALL
=======

	To compile all programs, simply type 'make' in the command-line, as
	shown below:

	$ make

	If you want to install the binaries in your home directory, you can type
	make install:

	$ make install

	Please remember to add ${HOME}/bin to your $PATH variable if you do so.
	If you have privileged access to the machine, you can type sudo make
	install-local, to install the binaries in /usr/local/bin.

	If you have any further questions, please contact one of the authors.

